  "feesApplyText": "Easthaus Limited is a member of The Property Ombudsman (TPO) redress scheme and are a registered member of the Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme. This is a client money protection scheme to ensure your money is handled in the correct manner. A copy of our CMP certificate can be found on our website or obtained by contacting the agent directly.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nEasthaus is committed to being upfront with our charges and fees. The below are payments you may be asked to make during the offer process to move into a property or during your tenancy:<br />\n<br />\n1.\tHolding Deposit: Equivalent to 1 weeks rent, payable once your offer has been accepted by the landlord. This is deducted from the monies due (rent in advance and security deposit) before the tenancy start date. The property is not considered under offer until a holding deposit has been received. Until that point, we cannot decline any other offers or cancel any further viewings. The holding deposit is refundable if the landlord decides not to offer a tenancy to you. The holding deposit is non-refundable if the tenant either: fails a Right to Rent check, withdraws from the application process, does not respond or contact us to progress the tenancy, or gives false or misleading information that affects their suitability as a tenant.<br />\n<br />\n2.\tRent in Advance: The agreed rent should be paid to Easthaus and received prior to the tenancy commencement date and before keys can be released.<br />\n<br />\n3.\tDeposit:  Five week s rent (six week s rent if the annual rent exceeds \u00a350,000). This will be protected in a Government approved scheme.<br />\n<br />\n4.\tLate payments:  If you are late in paying your rent you may be charged interest on the rent outstanding if it is owed for more than 14 days at a rate of 3% over the Bank of England base rate.<br />\n<br />\n5.\tContract amendments:  Changes to the tenancy agreement, e.g. a change of tenant or permission to keep pets at the property, will be charged at \u00a350.00 (plus reasonable costs if these exceed \u00a350.00).<br />\n<br />\n6.\tReplacement keys:  If you lose your keys or other security device you will be charged reasonable costs incurred by the landlord to replace these items or to replace the locks at the property.<br />\n<br />\n7.\tEarly termination:  If you leave or request to terminate the tenancy early, you will be liable to pay for any fees for re-letting and outstanding rent owed to the Landlord.",
